modules.description: Provides functions to create, update, and query dictionaries with string keys and arbitrary value types. Operates on associative arrays where keys are strings and values can be of any OCaml type. Enables efficient lookups and modifications in scenarios like configuration parsing or data mapping.

Provides hash folding, comparison, and S-expression conversion for dictionaries mapping strings to values. Constructs dictionaries from association lists, retrieves values by key, and converts between dictionaries and lists of key-value pairs. Designed for efficient lookups and static data structures where keys are known at creation.
